urity, Event Management, JAVA Design Standards, Application To Application Communication, Caching, etc. Propose new standards based on business need, IT need and technology advances. Assist development teams to implement the standards into business applications. Investigate new technology and techniques that should be developed into an agency enterprise architecture standard.&nbsp;<br />Manage and scrutinize information presented by Accela Inc. to ensure that it is in the best interest of the State of Michigan and that the solutions will function properly within the State of Michigan infrastructure and fits the needs of Licensing and Regulatory Affairs.&nbsp;<br />Leads key enterprise architectural design projects as necessary. Operate as business savvy technical leader across the organization. Influences development teams to design high-quality technical solutions that fit the Enterprise Architecture and standards. Educates application development managers, developers, and business analysts on State Enterprise Architecture Standards.&nbsp;<br /><br />Skills:&nbsp;<br />Required / Desired&nbsp;<br />Amount&nbsp;<br />of Experience&nbsp;<br />Experience implementing and supporting the Accela Civic Platform for Licensing and Case Management and Accela Citizen Access&nbsp;<br />Required&nbsp;<br />5&nbsp;<br />Years&nbsp;<br />Experience with reporting (SSRS and Crystal Reports)&nbsp;<br />Required&nbsp;<br />5&nbsp;<br />Years&nbsp;<br />Strong experience with Accela data migration using Accela Data migration tool&nbsp;<br />Required&nbsp;<br />5&nbsp;<br />Years&nbsp;<br />Experience in the IT industry with business analysis, design, development and testing&nbsp;<br />Required&nbsp;<br />5&nbsp;<br />Years&nbsp;<br />Experience in the IT industry with documentation and administration&nbsp;<br />Required&nbsp;<br />5&nbsp;<br />Years&nbsp;<br />Experience in the IT industry with implementation and supporting highly technical and complex information systems&nbsp;<br />