(5420, NULL, NULL, 3087, 0, NULL, 1, '', '43510//Applications Systems //FSSA -', NULL, '<div class="ExternalClass467807ADA13F4DE48A7D03E7E94428DA">\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<ul>\n<li>Attend (and/or facilitate)&#160;discussions between Deloitte IEDSS and RCR to track status of integration activities between the two entities. &#160;Ensure that the State''s interests and expectations are being fulfilled by tracking these discussions, as well as any issues/risks that arise&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</li>\n<li>Attend IEDSS &lt;-&gt; Data Warehouse discussions to ensure that data shared with Data Warehouse in relation to reports is tracked, documented, and kept up to date for DFR''s needs</li>\n<li>Keep business process documentation up to date (or create from scratch as needed) for all of the business processes associated with IEDSS. &#160;These are necessary for understanding processes, task management, and also for sharing with federal stakeholders as needed to signal compliance with their requirements, including MITA maturity</li>\n<li>Acting as liaison for business requirements, system design efforts, and other system development lifecycle (SDLC) activities between DFR and its design, development, and implementation (DDI) system vendors</li>\n<li>Track issues and risks in DDI SDLC activities and escalate to DFR as appropriate</li>\n<li>Create and/or update business process documentation in relation to how clients, workers, and other pertinent stakeholders have when leveraging the IEDSS solution</li>\n<li>Create and/or updated system and technical processes, as identified by DFR, related to IEDSS</li>\n<li>Attend DFR-determined meetings and track issues, action items, and risks that are identified in those discussions</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Required Background&#58;</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Software Development Lifecycle (SDLC) Best Practices</li>\n<li>Social Services Program (e.g., Medicaid, SNAP, TANF) eligibility subject matter expertise</li>\n</ul>\n<p><stron