(5422, NULL, NULL, 2867, 0, NULL, 1, '', 'Front End Developer', NULL, '<div class="ExternalClassE6FFF60B10054618A427ACE986541DCB">\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<p>JOB SUMMARY&#58; The Front-End Web Developer will bring coding expertise to the Client Customer websites. They will translate design mockups into usable HTML/CSS for responsive web pages that comply with 508 and WCAG accessibility requirements, working closely with other developers in IT to ensure successful integration of the web pages to Client?s back-end system. The developer will also evolve our responsively designed web properties, focusing on innovations in the digital landscape and adopting the website to new devices as they are adopted by our end users.</p>\n<p><br> The developer will be responsible for the design, development, and maintenance effort associated with Client?s large scale customer servicing web site. The web site is responsive by design, built to render optimally on multiple device types based upon Bootstraps 960 grid system, and architected in MVC (Model-View-Controller) pattern. The developer should have an understanding both agile and waterfall software development life cycle, and be prepared to participate in all phases of the SDLC (requirements analysis, high level design, detailed design, coding, unit test, integration, system level test) helping to create and review deliverables. The developer must be highly motivated and focused on completing tasks efficiently with high quality. Additional responsibilities may include assisting with code reviews, developing deliverable estimates, and coordinating software enhancements.</p>\n<p><br> <br> Skill Requirements</p>\n<p>&#160;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Utilize established development tools, guidelines and frameworks including but not limited to ASP.NET, SQL Server, HTML5, JSON, CSS3, JavaScript, and C# .NET, Bootstrap, RESTful technologies.</li>\n<li>Design, code and test new Windows and web software applications</li>\n<li>Maintain existi