(5452, NULL, 0, 2876, 0, NULL, 1, NULL, 'Business Analyst', NULL, '<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong>:</p>\n<p>Provides business systems analysis and process redesign expertise, interacting with business partners to clearly define and document User Stories.</p>\n<p>Define precise and accurate User Story acceptance criteria that will be used by developers, automation test frameworks and by product owners to ensure that product owner intent is effectively captured.</p>\n<p>Gather requirements for IT development projects by conducting interviews, work flow analysis, process analysis, and observation sessions.</p>\n<p>Evaluate information from multiple sources and help distinguish user requests from user needs.</p>\n<p>Understand systemic data requirements as they relate to enhancing/changing the business process or system.</p>\n<p>Participate and/or coordinate required testing/validation of system enhancements and fixes, creating and/or executing the test cases including problem determination and resolution.</p>\n<p>Utilize <strong>ClearCase</strong> for defeat tracking; Test Tools such as <strong>Rational Quality Manager (RQM) and JAWS.</strong></p>\n<p>Apply project management standards ensuring obstacles and risks are identified, tracked and escalated and communicates to team members and PM accordingly.</p>\n<p>Interface with all levels of internal clients and analyzing current business and software development processes.</p>\n<p>Facilitate and clarify customer business needs and translating them into application and operational requirements.</p>\n<p>Arrange client reviews of software under development, ensuring client satisfaction.</p>\n</body>\n</html>', '<div class="ExternalClass3ED5CE8A9FC2459388F1FD11B5A1FAEB"><ul style="width&#58;98%;margin&#58;0;padding&#58;0;list-style-type&#58;none;"><li>?&#160;&#160;11/30/2016 -kevinj</li><li style="border-bottom&#58;1px dashed #C3C3C3;padding&#58;0 0 7px 19px;">\n<html>\