(5488, NULL, NULL, 3079, 0, NULL, 1, '', 'Sr. UNIX Administrator', NULL, '<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<p>&nbsp;UNIX, Solaris, RedHat, A+, Network+, VMware, Windows</p>\n</body>\n</html>', '<div class="ExternalClassC5E114F6D6DB4A2ABA11EC8C11117C4A">\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<p><strong>Looking for an experienced Unix System Admin with Solaris exerience.&#160;</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Essential Functions of the Position&#58;</strong></p>\n<p>As a Solaris/UNIX Sr. System Administrator, your responsibilities will include&#58;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Develop and document project plans for management and customer review</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Recommend best practices for systems reliability, scalability, redundancy, and availability</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Maintain interfaces with external systems</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Maintain proper security posture for Solaris systems</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Participate in the upgrading of operating systems and design of systems enhancements</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Identify, analyze, and resolve system problems</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Provide system/equipment/specialized training and technical guidance</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Determine system specifications, input/output processes, and working parameters for hardware/software compatibility</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Provide on-call/remote after-hours support to priority incidents</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Monitor and maintain adequate backup and recovery of all Solaris systems</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Provides input for documentation on new or existing systems</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Maintain the integrity and security of servers and systems</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Maintain system documentation</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Strong commitment to the team and the organization''s success</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Maintain current knowledge of relevant technology as assigned</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Participate in special projects or tasks as required</p>\n</li>\n<li></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<div id="iCIMS_Expandable_Button">&#160;</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<h3 class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoField_Job">Qualifications&#160;&#160;</h3>\n<div class="iCIMS_InfoMsg iCIMS_InfoMsg_Job">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Container">\n<div class="iCIMS_Expandable_Text">\n<ul>\n<li>5-7 years of direct hands on experience with Unix and Linux Environments</li>\n<li>Experience&#160; working with Oracle Solaris Operating Systems, legacy containers/zones (brand-z containers), LDOMs, disk mirroring, ZFS, explorer, NFS, RBAC, Solaris 10/11, Sun, and virtual networks</li>\n<li>Experience with running Enterprise Linux Environments on VMware ESXi</li>\n<li>Applying Security Management practices to Unix servers&#58;&#160;</li>\n<li>Ability to install, configure and migrate domains.</li>\n<li>Solaris experience required</li>\n<li>Comprehensive knowledge of the principles, methods, and techniques used in systems administration and support</li>\n<li>Comprehensive knowledge of related hardware and software</li>\n<li>UNIX, Solaris, RedHat, A+, Network+, VMware, Windows</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Desired Skills&#58;</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Strong verbal and written communication skills</li>\n<li>Ability to communicate clearly with peers and managemen</li>\n<li>Excellent problem solving and analytical skills</li>\n<li>Excellent communication skills. Strong teamwork and engagement as a project team member</li>\n<li>Ability to assimilate information rapidly, motivated to self study new requirements</li>\n<li>Excellent documentation skills</li>\n<li>Strong organizational and collaborative skills</li>\n<li>Capacity to develop a clear understanding of the business needs and incorporate these needs into technical solutions</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</di