(5500, NULL, NULL, 3047, 0, NULL, 1, '', 'Senior Business Analyst', NULL, '<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<p>Working technical knowledge of Java, J2EE, advanced design patterns, and web services<br /> Demonstrated knowledge or experience overseeing the design, development, and implementation of software and hardware solutions, systems, or products.</p>\n<p>Experienced in supporting and executing full SDLC, from initial requirements analysis and software design through test case development, implementation, and enhancements</p>\n</body>\n</html>', '<div class="ExternalClass88986A6766BD438D86A122B07B13F161">\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<p><strong>Project Details</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Create and support fully automated and web-accessible anytime network dashboard for EHS and MassIT-monitored WAN circuits which automatically incorporates WAN data from new Secretariats brought on as part of OneNetwork</li>\n<li>Create and support fully automated and web-accessible anytime application dashboard for all data center applications and Wily-monitored (Java) EHS applications</li>\n<li>Expected outcomes and deliverables include&#58;</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Summary network metrics available online, on-demand in ?local? Splunk</li>\n<li>Network information updated automatically with new circuits, etc.</li>\n<li>?Local? Splunk data and dashboards migrated to production Splunk</li>\n<li>Operations teams trained on network dashboard</li>\n<li>Production Splunk configured for TMG log ingestion</li>\n<li>Application dashboard built in production Splunk</li>\n<li>Production Splunk ingesting TMG, F5, Ace load balancer logs</li>\n<li>Automated EHS Wily data pull POC</li>\n<li>EHS Wily ongoing automated data capture</li>\n<li>Operations trained on application dashboard</li>\n<li>LAN metrics definition/capture</li>\n<li>Support Metrics</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities&#58;</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Collaborate with stakeholders to determine project scope and vision.</li>\n<li>Conduct interviews and product analysis to gather user requirements via workshops, questionnaires, surveys, site visits, workflow storyboards, use cases, scenarios, and other methods.</li>\n<li>Develop and utilize standard templates to accurately and concisely write requirement specifications.</li>\n<li>Translate conceptual user requirements into functional requirements in a clear manner that is comprehensible to developers/project team.</li>\n<li>Where necessary, develop prototypes of interfaces and attributes based on findings.</li>\n<li>Analyze and verify requirements for completeness, consistency, comprehensibility, feasibility, and conformity to standards.</li>\n<li>Identify and establish scope and parameters of requirements analysis in order to define impact, outcome criteria, and measure-taking actions.</li>\n<li>Work with stakeholders and project team to prioritize collected requirements.</li>\n<li>Create process models, specifications, diagrams, and charts to provide direction to developers and/or the project team.</li>\n<li>Develop and conduct peer reviews to ensure that requirement specifications are correctly interpreted.</li>\n<li>Manage and track the status of requirements throughout the project lifecycle; enforce and redefine as necessary.</li>\n<li>Communicate changes, enhancements, and modifications ? verbally or through written documentation project managers, sponsors, and other stakeholders so that issues and solutions are understood.</li>\n<li>Research, review, and analyze the effectiveness and efficiency of existing requirements-gathering processes and develop strategies for enhancing or further leveraging these processes.</li>\n<li>Establish practices and procedures that work towards the continuous improvement of the requirements process.</li>\n<li>Integrate requirements into enterprise IT system level requirements</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>&#160;</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Qualifications&#58; </strong><em>Include a d