(5514, NULL, NULL, 3087, 0, NULL, 1, '', '45157//Helpdesk Service Specialist//Courts', NULL, '<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<p>Helpdesk</p>\n</body>\n</html>', '<div class="ExternalClass01DA31C9DC4C468298C2A48104E8A9D6">\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<p><strong>Essential Duties/Responsibilities &#58;</strong></p>\n<p>&#160;</p>\n<p>The position is responsible for assisting the Deputy Director of Appellate IT Operations in two areas&#58; replacement of computer equipment and migration of data files from obsolete servers to new platforms.&#160;</p>\n<p>&#160;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Assist technical staff and end-users with the replacement of desktop and notebook computers; this service will require the transfer of locally-stored data files, if any, to the user?s OneDrive for Business account in Office 365, as well as the transfer of the user?s system settings from the old to the new computer</li>\n<li>Manage service desk tickets from initiation through completion or assignment to colleagues; track progress, keep record of issue/request resolutions, etc.</li>\n<li>Install software and peripheral computer equipment; hardware, printers, monitors, etc.</li>\n<li>Assist technical staff with the transfer of data files from obsolete servers to new platforms, including SharePoint online, OneDrive for Business, and new Windows Server systems, as instructed by the Deputy Director</li>\n<li>Manage equipment and inventory; tag new assets, install and image new equipment for deployment, remove all proprietary data prior to surplus, etc.</li>\n<li>Provide general administrative support to the Appellate Court Technology Director</li>\n<li>Additional duties as assigned</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>&#160;</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Qualifications&#58; </strong></p>\n<p>&#160;</p>\n<h1>Accredited Associates degree in Information Technology and two (2) years of help desk, technical support, or related experience; OR accredited Bachelor?s degree and one (1) year of experience.&#160; Plus, a CompTIA A+ certification, or equivalent.</h1>\n<h1>&#160;</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>Windows Server ? intermediate level of proficiency, or higher, is required</li>\n<li>Windows 7/8/10 ? intermediate level of proficiency, or higher, is required</li>\n<li>SharePoint, OneDrive for Business, and Office 365 ? beginner level of proficiency, or higher, is desired but not required</li>\n<li>PowerShell script development is desired but not required</li>\n<li>Ability to lift and carry items weighing up to 50 pounds</li>\n</ul>\n</body>\n</html></div>', 'CR', '', '', '31', 'Awaiting', 0, NULL, '', '', 'USA', '2017-02-01 10:53:34', '2017-02-01 10:53:34', '2017-02-02 10:10:53', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '21', '2017-02-10 00:00:00', '', '\n\n\n\n\nHelpdesk\n\n', 'Hr', 'State of Indiana'),
(5515, NULL, NULL, 3087, 0, NULL, 1, '', '45159//Information Security Analyst//IOT', NULL, '<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<p>Information Security Analyst</p>\n</body>\n</html>', '<div class="ExternalClass3FCAFA7DAEB1477BAA6A1DB9FAD70407">\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<p><strong><u>Essential Duties/Responsibilities&#58;</u></strong></p>\n<p>&#160;</p>\n<p>This position is responsible for evaluating risks to MPH information resources, prioritizing concerns, and developing plans and projects to remediate risks.&#160; The position serves as the information security technical lead to the MPH team, providing evaluation of risks and guidance on remediation strategies.&#160; The position uses a multitude of tools to continually assess the MPH environment.&#160; The position serves as a liaison with IOT operational units and agency security leadership on acute security issues and ongoing projects.&#160; Direct development and oversight of appropriate controls as part of a risk management program and serving as a lead in testing potential technical solutions for their application in the MPH environment is another aspect of this position. Use knowledge and experience to identify risk</p>\n<p>&#160;</p>\n<p><strong><u>Job Requirements&#58; </u></strong></p>\n<p>&#160;</p>\n<p>Bachelor?s Degree or equivalent experience is required. CISSP is preferred but not a requirement if background has extensive diversity in various aspects of information security.&#160; Individual must be able to assess risk and communicate with the MPH team, other management positions and technical staff.&#160; Must be technically capable of leading the testing of security technologies that would improve MPH defensive capabilities.&#160; Must be able to proactively research threats to the environment and assist in response to attacks of various types.&#160; Must be able to work autonomously and switch gears on a moment''s notice if demanded by a crisis.&#160; Position should be effective at developing plans to build fundamental solutions that contain or limit risks rather than continuously treating symptoms.</p>\n<p>&#160;</p>\n<p><strong><u>Supervisory Responsibilities/Direct Reports&#58;</u></strong></p>\n<p>&#160;</p>\n<p>None</p>\n<p><strong><u>&#160;</u></strong></p>\n<p><strong><u>Difficulty of Work&#58;</u></strong></p>\n<p>&#160;</p>\n<p>Work is broad in scope requiring extensive knowledge of various operating systems, software, networking, applications, agency envrionments, and hardware in order to keep MPH information secure.</p>\n<p>&#160;</p>\n<p><strong><u>Responsibility&#58;</u></strong></p>\n<p>&#160;</p>\n<p>Work has a direct effect and impact on MPH and other agencies ability to protect confidential citizen information and other sensitive information. The position is a leader for other security positions and leads operational teams when the environment is dealing with a security event.</p>\n<p>&#160;</p>\n<p><strong><u>Personal Work Relationships&#58;</u></strong></p>\n<p>&#160;</p>\n<p>Employee interacts with a wide range of personnel from this agency, other state agencies, outside contractors, and various levels of management. Employee may be involved in large-scale projects with many different parties or may work in isolation.&#160; Employee must be able to tactfully gain information and cooperation from co-workers, vendors, and customers.</p>\n<p>&#160;</p>\n<p><strong><u>Physical Effort&#58;</u></strong></p>\n<p>&#160;</p>\n<p>This position requires little physical effort but may occasionally require the lifting of up to 75lbs.</p>\n<p>&#160;</p>\n<p><strong><u>Working Conditions&#58;</u></strong></p>\n<p><strong><u>&#160;</u></strong></p>\n<p>Excellent workig conditions with new PC equipment and State provided phone (optional). This position is part of a team environment.</p>\n</body>\n</html></div>', 'CDR', '', '', '72', 'Awaiting', 0, NULL, 'Indianapolis', 'Indiana', 'USA', '2017-02-01 14:00:08', '2017-02-01 14:00:08', '2017-02-03 15:32:49', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '52', '2017-02-10 00:00:00', '', '\n\n\n\n\nInformation Security Analyst\n\n', 'Hr', 'State of Indiana'),
(5516, NULL, NULL, 3087, 0, NULL, 1, '', '45165//Information Security Analyst//FSSA', NULL, '<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<p>Informatin security analyst</p>\n</body>\n</html>', '<div class="ExternalClassA6C9AC3AB6D34E6180C8FA76A67B6486">\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<p><strong>Description of Duties&#58;</strong></p>\n<p>- Coordinate the configuration and operation of the Security Information and Event Management system, which acts as a repository and analysis center for information received from elements of the security architecture and other sources which can then be evaluated for anomalies which may indicate miscreant behavior.</p>\n<p>- Coordinate SIEM activities with application and business owners as necessary.</p>\n<p>- Work with the sources of information received by the SIEM solution to ensure that the data are in the proper format and with the proper semantics to be interpreted meaningfully by the SIEM.</p>\n<p>- Develop and implement appropriate rulesets guiding how the SIEM distinguishes between anomalies warranting investigation vs. events that do not. This should also distinguish where practical between events which represent innocent user errors vs. those created by malicious actions.</p>\n<p>- Participate appropriately in any incident response activities, especially with respect to providing information from the SIEM that may be relevant to investigation and remediation.</p>\n<p>- Develop and report on metrics showing how the SIEM function is being properly implemented.</p>\n<p>- Advanced knowledge of SIEM, FIM, DLP, IDS/IPS, firewall and anti-virus/malware solutions. IBM QRadar and Tripwire experience highly preferred.</p>\n<p>Experience implementing policies, procedures and practices to meet PCI and SOC requirements.</p>\n<p>-Advanced knowledge of information security principles and practices&#58; security risk assessment standards, risk assessment methodologies, and vulnerability assessment.</p>\n<p>- Knowledge of forensic requirements and capabilities for collecting, preserving and presenting evidence (for example, admissibility, quality and completeness of evidence, chain of custody).</p>\n<p>- Knowledge of internal and external incident reporting requirements and procedures.</p>\n<p><strong>Skillset Requested&#58;</strong></p>\n<p>Operating Systems</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Windows Server (Intermediate) ? 3-5 years</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Programming Language/Development Tools</p>\n<ul>\n<li>MS .Net (Intermediate) ? 3-5 years</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Database Systems/Database Tools</p>\n<ul>\n<li>SQL Server (Intermediate) ? 3-5 years</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Frameworks/SLDs/Methodologies</p>\n<ul>\n<li>NIST 800-53, MARS-E &amp; Pub 1075 (Intermediate) ? 3-5 years</li>\n<li>Experiencing in validating enterprise application compliance with federal security regs is considered a plus.</li>\n</ul>\n</body>\n</html></div>', 'CR', '', '', '92', 'Awaiting', 0, NULL, 'Indianapolis', 'Indiana', 'USA', '2017-02-02 09:50:45', '2017-02-02 09:50:45', '2017-02-07 09:30:36', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '65', '2017-02-02 00:00:00', '', '\n\n\n\n\nInformatin security analyst\n\n', 'Hr', 'State of Indiana'),
(5517, NULL, NULL, 3087, 0, NULL, 1, '', '45166//SCRUM Master//BMV', NULL, '<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<p>SCRUM Master</p>\n</body>\n</html>', '<div class="ExternalClassBE47E1594D0548CB8DBD34517618898D">\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<p>Scrum Master with the following skills &amp; experience.</p>\n<p>&#160;</p>\n<p><strong>Duties</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Manage the activities of the Scrum team, leverage Agile principles, and actively direct the development processes as needed.&#160; Project management and meeting business needs are more important than strict adherence to standard Scrum methodologies and practices.</li>\n<li>Document and hold the team accountable to the development policies, procedures, processes, and metrics that reflect best development practices and Information Technology Department business objectives.&#160;</li>\n<li>Proactively identify and manage project risks and dependencies and raise awareness within the appropriate stakeholders.</li>\n<li>Be accountable for the development processes to ensure business readiness of the application and its quality at its release.</li>\n<li>Ensure timely, accurate, and clear communication is provided to the appropriate stakeholders.&#160;</li>\n<li>Deliver software releases on time and that meet the quality standards.&#160;</li>\n<li>Maintain proper document controls such that the documentation can be readily used for audits and metrics tracking.&#160; Maintain project metric documentation to support various releases.&#160; This documentation can change depending on the needs of the various projects.</li>\n<li>Work in conjunction with Managers of BA, Dev, and QA groups to achieve project reporting and project goals.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&#160;</p>\n<p><strong>Skills&#58;</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Demonstrable experience of Scrum Management</li>\n<li>Agile Experience</li>\n<li>Planning Experience</li>\n<li>Team Foundation Server experience</li>\n<li>Strong leader, goal-driven</li>\n</ul>\n<p