(5522, NULL, NULL, 3087, 0, NULL, 1, '', '45198//IOT//Business Systems Consultant', NULL, '<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<p>Business Systems Consultant</p>\n</body>\n</html>', '<div class="ExternalClassB2EB7E9D3A9A4BDC980FBE908967AA11">\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<p><strong>Essential Duties/Responsibilities&#58;</strong></p>\n<p>This individual is responsible for orders and repairs for telco services, and telecom systems throughout the State.&#160; Orders include, but are not limited to, moves/adds/changes for telephony systems, and telco services.&#160; When necessary this person may also be responsible of acquiring quotes for telco and telecom service orders.&#160; This person will utilize online web-enabled portals for ticketing, ordering, billing and tracking.&#160; This person will also assist other teams in coordinating action items for telecom service projects.&#160; This individual will provide tier 1 support for telecom issues when necessary and/or will be responsible for coordinating and managing service repair of all State telephony systems, and telco services throughout the life of the trouble ticket.&#160; Excellent customer service is the number one goal.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</p>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements&#58;</strong></p>\n<p>Minimum of a high school diploma required.&#160; Knowledge of telephony features and systems such as messaging, mobile wireless and pagers.&#160; General knowledge of PBX, KTS, VoIP, CAN, WAN and video is necessary. Minimum of 5 years job experience in Telecom Systems.&#160; Some project management skills needed.&#160; Excellent oral and written communication skills are required.&#160; Additional certifications are preferred.</p>\n</body>\n</html></div>', 'CDR', '', '', '45', 'Accepted', 0, NULL, 'Indianapolis', 'Indiana', 'USA', '2017-02-06 10:02:49', '2017-02-06 10:02:49', '2017-02-06 10:03:20', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '30', '2017-02-15 00:00:00', '', '\n\n\n\n\nBusiness Systems Consultant\n\n', 'Hr', 'State of Indiana'),
(5523, NULL, NULL, 7914, 0, NULL, 1, '', 'QBAN Spotfire', NULL, '<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n</body>\n</html>', '<div class="ExternalClass4F6A9B24A80E4442B28BEE191DF5ED08">\n<html>\n<head>\n</head>\n<body>\n<p>&#160;</p>\n<p><strong>Required</strong> ?</p>\n<p>?&#160; At least 3 years of production TIBCO Spotfire support experience</p>\n<p>?&#160; Experience installing, administering, tuning, and upgrading Spotfire 7.x on Windows Server 2012</p>\n<p>?&#160; Multi-node installation and configuration of tiered Spotfire reporting platform</p>\n<p>?&#160; Experience configuring the database connections and configurations</p>\n<p>?&#160; Experience with administrative activities, such as starting, stopping, reconfiguring and monitoring Spotfire server components</p>\n<p>?&#160; Experience with clustering &amp; high availability implementation for Spotfire</p>\n<p>?&#160; Experience migrating systems from test to production</p>\n<p>?&#160; Spotfire security setup, tuning and troubleshooting; backup and recovery</p>\n<p>?&#160; Experience in trouble shooting and performance tuning of Spotfire web servers</p>\n<p>?&#160; Proven analytical and problem solving skills</p>\n<p>?&#160; Ability to work in a project-based environment with tight dead-lines</p>\n<p>?&#160; Customer focused with dedication to customer satisfaction</p>\n<p>?&#160; Experience with best practice methodologies such as ITIL</p>\n<p>?&#160; Knowledge and experience with SQL/DB Activities</p>\n<p>?&#160; As part of the Spotfire admin team, provide 24/7 on call support for the various enterprise systems</p>\n<p><strong>Nice to have</strong> ?</p>\n<p>?&#160; Oracle Business Intelligence (OBIEE) 11g and 12c support experience</p>\n<p>?&#160; ETLs and data analysis experience</p>\n</body>\n</html></div>', 'CR', '', '', '', 'Awaiting', 0, NULL, 'Banglore', 'Karnataka', 'INDIA', '2017-02-06 10:21:16', '2017-02-06 10:21:16', '2017-02-06 10:33:43', 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '2017-02-06