(5544, 192, -1, 2876, 192, 192, 1, '', 'EDI Developer', '', '<p class="MsoNormal"><strong><u><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif">Job Description:</span></u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif">The Executive\r\nOffice of Health and Human Services is looking for a senior EDI-X12 developer\r\nwho has a good understanding of health care claims processing, brings extensive\r\nworking knowledge with the X12 specification (and 820 and 834 standards in\r\nparticular), and is intimately familiar with Orion Health&rsquo;s Rhapsody product\r\nhaving designed and implemented solutions for a health care insurance provider\r\nor state Medicaid group.&nbsp; The ideal\r\ncandidate will be driven, need little supervision, and will possess all of the\r\nskills listed and hit the ground running in a fast-paced, high visibility\r\nenvironment.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong><u><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif">Requirements:</span></u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif">The ideal\r\ncandidate will have the following skills:&nbsp;\r\n</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: 115%" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: Symbol">&middot;<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif">Experience\r\nwith building interfaces using Orion Health Rhapsody Interface Engine,\r\ncertification is a plus.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: 115%" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: Symbol">&middot;<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif">Strong\r\nexperience with healthcare EDI transactions (X12), especially with the X12 820,\r\n834 messaging standards.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: 115%" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: Symbol">&middot;<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif">Experience\r\nwith Java/Javascript, XML/XLST.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: 115%" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: Symbol">&middot;<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif">Experience\r\nwith Server Operating Systems (both Windows &amp;Linux an advantage),\r\nClustering and Load Balancing (an advantage).</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: 115%" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: Symbol">&middot;<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif">Good\r\ncommunication skills.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0in">\r\n <li class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif">EDI-X12\r\n     Developer will be required to support the team in the following manner: </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt 1in; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: 115%" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: ''Courier New''">o<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif">Bring\r\nan additional perspective to the team based on knowledge of the 820, 834\r\nstandards and their proper use in Claims Management</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt 1in; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: 115%" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: ''Courier New''">o<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif">Assist\r\nor lead design and code reviews and signs-off on artifacts from all project\r\nphases.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt 1in; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: 115%" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: ''Courier New''">o<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif">Install\r\nOrion Rhapsody product and deploy completed software builds.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt 1in; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: 115%" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: ''Courier New''">o<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif">Solid\r\nfamiliarity with an RDBMS (preferably Oracle)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt 1in; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: 115%" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: ''Courier New''">o<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif">Strong\r\nRhapsody development skills and familiarity with most aspects of a recent\r\nversion of&nbsp; the Rhapsody tool</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt 1in; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: 115%" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: ''Courier New''">o<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif">Perform\r\nOrion Rhapsody maintenance, performance tuning, and support tasks.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt 1in; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: 115%" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: ''Courier New''">o<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif">Interact\r\nwith the Project Manager and Project Team to ensure the solution is delivered\r\non time and meets project requirements.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt 1in; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: 115%" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: ''Courier New''">o<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif">Preparation\r\nand maintenance of technical documentation for project team.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong><u><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif">About Tech Refresh Phase II program:</span></u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 0in 5.9pt 0.0001pt 0in; line-height: 102%" class="MsoBodyText"><span style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 102%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif">The\r\nproject will focus on the replacement a key piece of off-the-shelf software\r\n(The EDI Translation Engine) which is at end of life and must be replaced to\r\nstay compliant with CMS requirements and avoid security concerns. The EDI\r\nTranslation Engine converts files from the CMS-mandated standard to an internal\r\nformat used by MMIS.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" class="MsoNormalTable" style="margin-left: -0.55in; border-collapse: collapse">\r\n <tbody><tr>\r\n  <td width="691" valign="top" style="width: 7.2in; padding: 0in 5.4pt"><a name="_GoBack" title="_GoBack"></a>\r\n  <p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10pt; line-height: 107%">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n  </td>\r\n </tr>\r\n</tbody></table>', '', 'C', '0-3 months', '90', '', 'Closed', 0, 1, 'Quincy', 'Massachusetts', 'USA', NULL, '2017-02-27 16:37:45', '2017-03-24 12:18:09', 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, '75', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(5545, 191, -1, 3958, 191, 191, 1, '', 'Database Administrator/45446/BMV', '', '<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Project\r\nDetails: </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Role:\r\nSQL Server DBA with T-SQL</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Location:\r\nIndianapolis, IN</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Duration:\r\nLong-Term</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Visa:\r\nUSC, GC &amp; H1B</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Interview\r\nCriteria: Telephonic + In-Person</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Job\r\nDescription: </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">The\r\nDatabase Administrator&lsquo;s role is to design, install, monitor, maintain, and\r\nperformance tune production databases while ensuring high levels of data\r\navailability.&nbsp;&nbsp; This individual will also coordinate with the Senior\r\nDatabase Administrator for developing, implementing, and overseeing database\r\npolicies and procedures to ensure the integrity and availability of databases\r\nand their accompanying software.&nbsp;&nbsp; Position reports to Senior\r\nDatabase Administrator.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 5pt 0in 0.0001pt 0.25in" class="m7184348593421243431msolistparagraph"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&Oslash;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt">&nbsp; </span><span style="font-family: Cambria,serif">Monitor and optimize daily performance</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 5pt 0in 0.0001pt 0.25in" class="m7184348593421243431msolistparagraph"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&Oslash;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt">&nbsp; </span><span style="font-family: Cambria,serif">Create and monitor scheduled jobs</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 5pt 0in 0.0001pt 0.25in" class="m7184348593421243431msolistparagraph"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&Oslash;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt">&nbsp; </span><span style="font-family: Cambria,serif">Writing database documentation, including\r\ndata standards, procedures, and definitions for the data dictionary.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 5pt 0in 0.0001pt 0.25in" class="m7184348593421243431msolistparagraph"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&Oslash;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt">&nbsp; </span><span style="font-family: Cambria,serif">Controlling access permissions and\r\nprivileges</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 5pt 0in 0.0001pt 0.25in" class="m7184348593421243431msolistparagraph"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&Oslash;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt">&nbsp; </span><span style="font-family: Cambria,serif">Creation of indexes for performance\r\noptimization</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 5pt 0in 0.0001pt 0.25in" class="m7184348593421243431msolistparagraph"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&Oslash;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt">&nbsp; </span><span style="font-family: Cambria,serif">Proficiency with T-SQL language</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 5pt 0in 0.0001pt 0.25in" class="m7184348593421243431msolistparagraph"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&Oslash;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt">&nbsp; </span><span style="font-family: Cambria,serif">Capacity planning</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 5pt 0in 0.0001pt 0.25in" class="m7184348593421243431msolistparagraph"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&Oslash;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt">&nbsp; </span><span style="font-family: Cambria,serif">Five years experience in Microsoft SQL\r\nServer 2005/2008 database administration/development required.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 5pt 0in 0.0001pt 0.25in" class="m7184348593421243431msolistparagraph"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&Oslash;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt">&nbsp; </span><span style="font-family: Cambria,serif">Data Warehouse experience would be\r\nhelpful.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin: 5pt 0in 0.0001pt 0.25in" class="m7184348593421243431msolistparagraph"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&Oslash;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt">&nbsp; </span><span style="font-family: Cambria,serif">Experience with Compuware&rsquo;s suite of\r\nproducts a plus.</span></p>', '', 'C', '0-6 months', '71', '', 'Closed', 0, 1, 'Indianpolis', 'Indiana', 'USA', NULL, '2017-02-28 13:04:41', '2017-03-17 14:46:16', 0, 5, 0, 1, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(5546, 192, -1, 1, 192, 192, 1, '', 'Spotfire Admin - QBAN', '', '<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.75in" class="MsoListParagraph"><strong>Required</strong> &ndash; </p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoListParagraph"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&uuml;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif">&nbsp; </span>At least 3 years of production TIBCO\r\nSpotfire support experience</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoListParagraph"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&uuml;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif">&nbsp; </span>Experience installing, administering,\r\ntuning, and upgrading Spotfire 7.x on Windows Server 2012</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoListParagraph"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&uuml;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif">&nbsp; </span>Multi-node installation and\r\nconfiguration of tiered Spotfire reporting platform</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoListParagraph"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&uuml;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif">&nbsp; </span>Experience configuring the database\r\nconnections and configurations</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoListParagraph"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&uuml;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif">&nbsp; </span>Experience with administrative\r\nactivities, such as starting, stopping, reconfiguring and monitoring Spotfire\r\nserver components</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoListParagraph"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&uuml;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif">&nbsp; </span>Experience with clustering &amp; high\r\navailability implementation for Spotfire</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoListParagraph"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&uuml;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif">&nbsp; </span>Experience migrating systems from test\r\nto production</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoListParagraph"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&uuml;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif">&nbsp; </span>Spotfire security setup, tuning and\r\ntroubleshooting; backup and recovery</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoListParagraph"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&uuml;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif">&nbsp; </span>Experience in trouble shooting and\r\nperformance tuning of Spotfire web servers</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoListParagraph"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&uuml;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif">&nbsp; </span>Proven analytical and problem solving\r\nskills</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoListParagraph"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&uuml;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif">&nbsp; </span>Ability to work in a project-based\r\nenvironment with tight dead-lines</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoListParagraph"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&uuml;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif">&nbsp; </span>Customer focused with dedication to\r\ncustomer satisfaction</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoListParagraph"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&uuml;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif">&nbsp; </span>Experience with best practice\r\nmethodologies such as ITIL</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoListParagraph"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&uuml;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif">&nbsp; </span>Knowledge and experience with SQL/DB\r\nActivities</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&uuml;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif">&nbsp; </span>As part of the Spotfire admin team,\r\nprovide 24/7 on call support for the various enterprise systems</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.75in" class="MsoNormal"><strong>Nice to have</strong> &ndash; </p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&uuml;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif">&nbsp; </span>Oracle Business Intelligence (OBIEE)\r\n11g and 12c support experience</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Wingdings">&uuml;</span><span style="font-size: 7pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif">&nbsp; </span>ETLs and data analysis experience</p>', '', 'C', '0-6 months', '', '', 'On-Hold/Manager reviewing resumes', 0, 1, 'Banglore', 'Karnataka', 'India', NULL, '2017-02-28 13:44:09', '2017-03-24 12:23:45', 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(5547, 192, -1, 3047, 192, 192, 1, '', 'Desktop Support', '', '<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">Responsibilities</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nTake incoming calls and emails from Mass HIway participants and triage to the\r\nappropriate group to further resolve. This could be working with the Mass HIway\r\nvendor for the SaaS component or working with internal Mass HIway developers on\r\nlocally supported applications. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nRespond to reports of issues or questions from participants, coordinate the\r\nrepair effort or solving of the issue/question, and ensure re-establishment of\r\ngood relations following event resolution.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nConduct reviews of documents submitted by organizations and validate\r\neligibility for use in relation to the Mass HIway.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nProvide prospective Mass HIway Participants with additional information and\r\nguidance.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nProvide support to the Mass HIway Business Operations team to ensure proper\r\ntransition steps are followed and knowledge transfer occurs during a\r\nParticipant&rsquo;s migration from test to production use of the Mass HIway.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nCoordinate closely with other members of the Mass HIway team to optimize\r\nsupport for Mass HIway Participants.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nBuild relationships with Mass HIway Participants.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nDrive Participant satisfaction through exceptional customer service.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nAdvocate internally for the Participant&rsquo;s interests.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nWork closely with the technical team to ensure a solid technical\r\nimplementation.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nInfluence the technical team when needed to gain consensus on the selection of\r\nthe most viable solution based on the customer service calls that are received.\r\n</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nKeep tracking systems updated and participate in internal reporting processes.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nDocument production incidents and other needs as directed by the manager.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nHelp define, document, and improve business and technical operations processes.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nAssist Mass HIway management and team members with other activities, as\r\nrequired.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">Qualifications:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">Applicants must have at least (A) Three years of\r\nfull-time, or equivalent part-time, professional experience in IT Customer\r\nSupport, or (B) any equivalent combination of the required experience and the\r\nsubstitutions below.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">Substitutions:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">I. An Associate''s degree with a major in the field of\r\ndata processing or computer programming may be substituted for a maximum of one\r\nyear of the required (A) experience.* </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">II. A Bachelor''s or higher degree with a major in the\r\nfield of data processing or computer and/or information science may be\r\nsubstituted for a maximum of one year of the required (A) experience.* </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">III. A diploma for completion of a two year full-time, or\r\nequivalent part-time, program in a recognized non-degree granting business or\r\nvocational/technical school above the high school level with a major in the\r\nfield of computer programming may be substituted for a maximum of one year of\r\nthe required (A) experience.*</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Education toward such a degree will be prorated on the\r\nbasis of the proportion of the requirements actually completed.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">Preferred Qualifications &amp; Skills:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nCustomer Support background and experience</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nExcellent written, verbal communication and interpersonal skills</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nStrong Microsoft Office skills</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nOrganization Skills</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nExperience with web application support</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nAbility to multi-task</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nWell-developed critical and analytical thinking and problem-solving skills</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\nEffectively coordinate between multiple teams</span></p>', '', 'C', '0-6 months', '40', '', 'On-Hold/Manager reviewing resumes', 0, 1, 'boston', 'Massachusetts', 'USA', NULL, '2017-02-28 17:21:31', '2017-03-24 12:35:11', 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(5548, 192, -1, 1, 192, 192, 1, '', 'IT - Release & Environment Manager Quintles', '', '<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">RESPONSIBLITIES:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Produce&nbsp; and maintain\r\ndocumentation for IT and customer-driven projects</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Align all aspects of the end to\r\nend release process</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Ensures coordination of all\r\nplatform environments</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Ensures teams follow the\r\norganization''s established policies and procedures</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Provides management reports on\r\nenvironment and release alignment</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Service release and deployment\r\npolicy and planning</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Deals with release package\r\nacceptance including business sign off</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Coordinates release testing to\r\npredefined acceptance criteria</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Owns documentation and\r\nartifacts for production releases</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Validates release acceptance\r\nfrom customers and stakeholders prior to implementation</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Deals with communication,\r\npreparation and training</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Aligns agile software delivery\r\nwith change control processes.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Project manages the delivery of\r\nnew platform implementations.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Develop process to track\r\nenvironments required for releases</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Create short-term plans to\r\ndeliver environments to support sprint-based development</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Coordinate activities of\r\ndevelopment to automate the setup and configuration of environments</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Communicate environment\r\navailability to project management and quality assurance</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Resolve conflicts between teams\r\ncompeting for limited environments</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Move environment activities\r\ntoward a goal of 100% automation</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Provide estimates for\r\nonboarding of new projects to environments</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Design systems to support\r\ncontinuous delivery and adapt environment management to support on-demand,\r\nself-service automation</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Forecast environment\r\nrequirements based on anticipated future demand from multiple application\r\ndevelopment teams</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Forward Plan the release\r\nwindows and cycles across a portfolio</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Manage risks and resolves\r\nissues that affect release scope, schedule and quality</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Measure and monitor progress to\r\nensure application releases are delivered on time and within budget, and that\r\nthey meet or exceed expectations</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Communicate all key project\r\nplans, commitments, and changes including requirements, QA plans, schedule, and\r\nscope changes</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Manage relationships and\r\ncoordinate work between different teams at different locations</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Conduct Release Readiness\r\nreviews, Milestone Reviews, and Business Go/No-Go reviews</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Produce Deployment, Run Books\r\nand Implementation Plans</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Weekly Release Reporting</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Communicate release details and\r\nschedules to the Business as required</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Negotiate, plan and manage all\r\nrelease activities</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Maintains the release schedule\r\nfor all core services and ensure alignment across key partners and vendors.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Continually work towards making\r\nimprovements in the release process</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Lead and co-ordinate the\r\nGo-Live activities including the execution of the deployment Plans and\r\nchecklists.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Participate in CAB meetings to\r\ndiscuss release scope and/or roadblocks</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Maintains a release repository\r\nand manages key information such as build and release procedures, dependencies,\r\nand notification lists</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Researches new software\r\ndevelopment and configuration management methodologies and technologies and\r\nanalyzes their application to current configuration management needs</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong><span style="color: #1f497d">Qualifications</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #1f497d">REQUIRED KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS AND\r\nABILITIES</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*2-6 years of previous release\r\nand/or project management experience, (Solid understanding of project\r\nmanagement principles preferred)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*8-10 years of experience in\r\ninformation systems operations environment in systems analysis or development</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Formal training in project\r\nmanagement practices preferred</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Advanced knowledge of software\r\ndevelopment lifecycle</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Demonstrated effective\r\nleadership and analytical skills</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Advanced written and verbal\r\ncommunication skills are a must</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Microsoft Project experience a\r\nplus</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Worked with Agile tools such as\r\nJira, Confluence and Bamboo</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong><span style="color: #1f497d">MINIMUM REQUIRED EDUCATION\r\nAND EXPERIENCE</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Candidate should have a minimum\r\nof 5-7 years project management experience, strong communication and\r\ninterpersonal skills; or equivalent combination of education, training, and\r\nexperience.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #1f497d">*Bachelor''s degree in Computer\r\nScience or related field</span></p>', 'CLient: Quintles', 'C2H', '0-3 months', '', '', 'On-Hold/Manager reviewing resumes', 0, 1, 'Boston', 'Massachusetts', 'USA', NULL, '2017-03-01 10:52:21', '2017-03-27 12:55:29', 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
