(5576, 1265, -1, 2876, 1265, 1265, 1, '', 'Telecommunications Engineer/Project Manager', 'Telecommunications Engineer/Project Manager', '<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Position Summary: </strong><br />\r\nThe City of Boston Department of Innovation and Technology (DoIT) is seeking a\r\nTelecommunications Analyst/Engineer, with project management expertise, for the\r\nMetro Boston Homeland Security Region (MBHSR).&nbsp; The contracted analyst\r\nwill conduct an analysis on the feasibility of connecting the City&rsquo;s 10GB fiber\r\noptic network infrastructure, called BoNet, to designated surrounding towns&rsquo;\r\npublic safety networks via existing fiber.&nbsp; The designated public safety\r\nentities are part of the MBHSR which include the following municipalities:\r\nBoston, Brookline, Cambridge, Chelsea, Everett, Quincy, Revere, Somerville and\r\nWinthrop.&nbsp; This position is funded for up to 6 months.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">The ideal candidate will have at least ten years of\r\nexperience in fiber optic construction and connectivity along with in-depth\r\nknowledge of existing fiber and conduit runs throughout the MBHSR.&nbsp; This\r\nposition requires a balance of technical knowledge of fiber optic and network\r\ndeployments along with strong project and vendor management skills.&nbsp; The\r\nkey deliverable from this analysis will be the documented solutions for\r\nconnectivity to each Region from BoNet.&nbsp; The candidate must have the\r\nability to travel around the Region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal">Establish a working relationship with public safety and\r\n     city/town IT staff throughout the Region.</li>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal">Review fiber and conduit maps in various formats as\r\n     produced by each municipality. </li>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal">Discuss options for fiber connectivity with each\r\n     municipality and the appropriate fiber vendors.</li>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal">Work with the City&rsquo;s BoNet Network Manager and\r\n     Engineering team for designing fiber and network connectivity options.</li>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal">Work with the City&rsquo;s Project Manager to review tasks,\r\n     time schedules, deliverables and next steps. </li>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal">Document and map options for fiber connectivity using\r\n     ARCGIS, CAD or another City-approved application.</li>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal">Develop detailed plans for implementing proposed fiber\r\n     connectivity solutions; include justifications, risk assessments, possible\r\n     roadblocks and cost estimates.</li>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal">Provide advice and act as a fiber connectivity subject\r\n     matter expert for the Region.</li>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal">Identify and solve fiber connectivity issues.</li>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal">Perform related work as required.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-top: 12pt" class="MsoNormal"><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal">Minimum 10 years of fiber telecommunications\r\n     experience.</li>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal">Working knowledge of the following design and\r\n     installation standards as they apply to fiber optics:</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 1in; text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoNormal"><!--[if !supportLists]-->-<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><!--[endif]-->BICSI Design and Installation Applicable\r\nStandards</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 1in; text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoNormal"><!--[if !supportLists]-->-<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><!--[endif]-->Telecommunications Industry Association (TIA)\r\nApplicable Standards</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 1in; text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoNormal"><!--[if !supportLists]-->-<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><!--[endif]-->ANSI/TIA/EIA &ndash; 568 Standards</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 1in; text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoNormal"><!--[if !supportLists]-->-<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><!--[endif]-->ANSI/TIA/EIA &ndash; 569 Standards</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 1in; text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoNormal"><!--[if !supportLists]-->-<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><!--[endif]-->TIA/EIA 604 Fiber Optic Standards</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 1in; text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoNormal"><!--[if !supportLists]-->-<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><!--[endif]-->TIA-492 Fiber Optic Installation Standards</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 1in; text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoNormal"><!--[if !supportLists]-->-<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><!--[endif]-->TSB-149 Fiber Optic Workmanship Standards</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal">Proficient in identifying fiber and conduit runs by\r\n     owner within the MBHSR.</li>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal">Proficient in mapping applications, preferably ARCGIS.</li>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal">Valid driver&rsquo;s license and ability to travel within the\r\n     MBHSR Region.</li>\r\n <li class="MsoNormal">Former public safety and local, state, federal\r\n     government experience preferred.</li>\r\n</ol>', '', 'C', '6-12 months', '100', '', 'Lost', 0, 1, 'Boston', 'Massachusetts', 'USA', NULL, '2017-03-27 15:10:09', '2017-04-12 09:05:27', 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
