(5582, 191, -1, 3958, 191, 191, 1, '', '46142//Business Analyst//ISDH', '', '<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Essential\r\nDuties/Responsibilities:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">1. Review and analyze Electronic Lab data quality issues, at\r\nan agency level.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">2. Ability to manage complex projects and tasks (multiple\r\nsystems, program areas).</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">3. Maintain overall daily helpdesk support to all users of\r\nNBS &amp; DREX; to include (but not limited to) resolution of helpdesk tickets,\r\ncollaborating with the development team to create new user accounts an</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">4. Maintain the existing accounts, and communicating\r\nregularly with NBS&amp; DREX users for guidance in using the application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">5. Develop a testing work plan to be used in instances of\r\nnew development within the application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">6. Provide assistance to the program areas as they schedule\r\nand execute user trainings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">7. Develop and update other training materials for\r\npresentation as required. Publish various notices regarding NBS&amp; DREX;\r\nincluding system updates, Quick Reference Guides (QRGs), announcements for\r\ntraining opportunities, and general updates on the status of NBS&amp; DREX\r\ntraining. This task is on-going as required.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">8. Works with four divisions within ISDH (OTC, TB, ERC, STD)\r\non strategic direction and status of the NBS&amp; DREX support activities. </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">9. Participate as part of the NBS &amp; DREX core-team, and\r\nthe NBS &amp; DREX User Panel to discuss future direction of I- NEDSS. </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">10. Be the lead on all NBS user panel calls. </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">11. Present at state and National Conferences about NBS.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">12. Provide testing and business analysis support for QA\r\nsystem releases before migration to the production</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">13. Report problems and findings to core team for follow up.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">14. Participate in conferences and provide NBS&amp; DREX\r\nmarketing and promotional materials in order to encourage new and continued\r\nNBS&amp; DREX use.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">15. Other duties as assigned.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">1. Pr<a name="_GoBack" title="_GoBack"></a>oven analytical and SQL skills.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">2. Significant knowledge on Communicable Diseases</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">3. Knowledge of Electronic labs &ndash; HL7 format 2.3.1 and 2.5.1</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">4. Knowledge and experience with Visio (showing workflow\r\netc)</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">5. A proven track record with enterprise analysis</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">6. Knowledge of creating SAS reports (preferred)</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">7. Experience in leading other Business Analysts</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">8. Ability to adapt to change</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">9. Proven organization, communication, leadership, and\r\nproblem-solving skills. (required)</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">10. User-level Experience with Microsoft Office Suite,\r\nincluding Outlook, Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Publisher, and Access. (required)</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">11. Proven ability to self-manage and complete contract\r\ndeliverables. (required)</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">12. Experience in public health or medical related industry.\r\n(preferred)</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">13. Experience with NBS or other disease surveillance systems.\r\n(preferred)</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">14. Experience with development and presentation of training\r\nmaterials. (preferred)</p>', '', 'C', '0-3 months', '58', '', 'Closed', 0, 1, 'indianapolis', 'Indiana', 'USA', '2017-04-10 00:00:00', '2017-03-29 17:05:30', '2017-04-20 10:50:59', 0, 15, 0, 1, NULL, '45', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
