(5593, 1253, -1, 3112, 1253, 1253, 1, '', 'Enrollment Specialist', 'Enrollment Specialist , Healthcare', '<p>Job responsibilities &ndash;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Health Plan Commercial Group (Fully-insured and Self-funded) Member Enrollment <strong>operations</strong> experience including paper, email/fax, electronic enrollments (not call center experience)</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&bull; Assist external and internal customers with enrollment related inquires</p><p>Should have managed at least a small BPO Enrollment Team</p><p>Should know how to create SOP&rsquo;s and Business Process</p><p>Should have Billing Operations experience (Premium Invoice - Review and Reconciliation)</p><p>&bull; Assist in New Group Implementation</p><p>&bull; Auditing Records</p><p>&bull; Review and process enrollment questions and appeals per the Plan Document</p><p>&bull; Providing excellent client services</p><p>&bull; Communicating with outside clients and vendors</p><p>&bull; Processing COB, dependent maximum age, open enrollment</p><p>&bull; Processing enrollments via paper, online or electronic file</p><p>&bull; Work on Enrollment Errors</p><p>&bull; Part of the Enrollment Team</p><p>&bull; Create Standard Operating Procedures for Enrollment</p><p>&bull; Travel up to 30% of the time</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>SkillSet &ndash;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&bull; BA/BS degree preferred with at least Six (6) years of relevant professional experience in Healthcare enrollment and billing operations for a large</p><p>national/regional/blue plan</p><p>&bull; Excellent Business Analysis Skills</p><p>&bull; Extensive experience in developing standard operating procedures (SOPs) and processes for Healthcare enrollment and billing operations</p><p>&bull; Excellent verbal and written communication skills</p><p>&bull; Proficiency with web-based/Client Server processing software platforms</p><p>&bull; Proficiency with MS Office applications, especially Word, Excel, Visio</p><ul><li>Should have managed at least a small BPO E