(5633, 192, -1, 3958, 192, 192, 1, '', 'Application Systems Analyst/Programme/46766/CHE', '', '<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Essential\r\nDuties/Responsibilities:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&bull; Maintain, test, and support the core student financial aid\r\napplications, data submission applications, and other applications</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&bull; Design, develop, and implement applications and system\r\nprocess improvements to integrate applications, add needed functionality,\r\nresolve issues with logic or data, and protect student data </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&bull; Prepare detailed project feasibility studies, formulate\r\ncomplete system scope, project cost, time estimates and human resource and IT\r\ninfrastructure requirements for new and existing application software systems</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&bull; Prepare detailed documentation/Standard Operating\r\nProcedures (SOP) for new or modified information systems and/or application\r\nsoftware programs, including operational procedures and manuals</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&bull; Assist end users with training and questions related to\r\nstudent financial aid applications</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&bull; Help review and test business continuity/disaster recovery\r\nplan for student financial aid applications and other ICHE information systems</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&bull; Other duties as assigned&nbsp;\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&bull; Solid understanding of agency mission and programs\r\n(http://www.in.gov/che); ability to work in a team environment with minimal\r\nsupervision. Demonstrated self-motivation, attention-to-detail and initiative\r\nrequired</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&bull; Demonstrated ability to communicate effectively,\r\nprofessionally, and assertively with coworkers and stakeholders. Demonstrated\r\nability to lead discussion with technical and non-technical coworkers</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&bull; Bachelor&rsquo;s degree plus five years of experience; ability\r\nto read and understand complicated technical manuals</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&bull; Experience maintaining codebases of large existing\r\napplications&nbsp; </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&bull; Advanced knowledge in the following application and\r\nprogramming languages:&nbsp; Microsoft Visual\r\nStudio, C#, ASP.NET, T-SQL, and XML. Solid understanding of relational database\r\ndesign principles and techniques in SQL Server, SSRS, and SSIS</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&bull; Familiarity with version control, used to identify changes\r\nin source, solution, configuration, and other files (preferred)</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&bull; Familiarity with Angular, Entity Framework and ASP.NET MVC\r\n(preferred) </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&bull; Familiarity with Data Warehousing principles and design,\r\nETL, SSAS, SSRS, and SAS (preferred)</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&bull; Demonstrated problem-solving and analytical proficiency\r\nand careful attention to detail, while managing multiple application\r\ndevelopment software projects and priorities</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Difficulty of Work:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Work is specialized involving complex program elements,\r\nwhich require technical and analytical abilities.&nbsp; Mature judgment and the ability to work under\r\nintense scrutiny are essential to the position.&nbsp;\r\nIncumbent must effectively coordinate work activities in a\r\nsemi-autonomous team environment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Responsibility:<a name="_GoBack" title="_GoBack"></a></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">This position has a direct and significant influence and\r\nimpact on the Commission''s ability to successfully administer approximately\r\n$275 million in student financial aid to over 100,000 Hoosier students\r\nannually.&nbsp; Failure to carry out this\r\nfunction successfully, in a timely manner and within the dollars allocated for\r\nsuch awards would be disastrous to Hoosier students and the Indiana colleges\r\nand universities they attend. Unusual problems or results are must be discussed\r\nwith supervisor.</p>', '', 'C2H', '0-6 months', '74', '', 'Closed', 0, 1, 'Indianapolis', 'Indiana', 'USA', NULL, '2017-05-08 11:00:56', '2017-06-29 09:55:40', 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL);
