p class="MsoNormal">Lead Analysts is expected to master the underlying data and\r\nbecome a &quot;go to&quot; resource for data questions and resolution,\r\nincluding providing future solutions. </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Primary accountability is to maintain Business Intelligence\r\ntools inclusive of Salesforce.com, Marketing Cloud and Tableau dashboards to\r\nprovide leaders consistent, accurate insight to make strategic business\r\ndecisions, meet regulatory requirements and execute on business opportunities. </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Lead Analysts is expected to master the underlying data and\r\nbecome a &quot;go to&quot; resource for data questions and resolution,\r\nincluding providing future solutions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Under direction of team leaders, Lead Analyst will create\r\nad-hoc analysis based on specific business queries. </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">The analysis performed may drive the development of future\r\ndashboards and creation of business requirements for additional data feeds.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">As a Marketing liaison, participate in ongoing Business,\r\nTechnology, Finance meetings to ensure deployment pipeline aligns with\r\nMarketing Cloud (and other Marketing business technology) needs. </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Incumbent will manage BME (change control) where Marketing\r\ntools impact SFDC or other connected business managed technologies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">Provide guidance on necessary metrics from Marketing Cloud\r\ndriven programs, including the design of Tableau dashboards to share results\r\nbroadly. Ability to articulate metrics needed by varying level from Senior\r\nLeadership to Internal Sales Desk.</p>', '', 'C', '6-12 months', '', '', 'Active', 0, 1, 'Boston', 'Massachusetts', 'USA', NULL, '2017-07-06 14:22:31', '2017-07-06 14:22:31', 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, '65-70', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
