riteria&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Accountable to the assigned Project Manager for all phases of specific projects.&nbsp;</div><div><br /></div><div>Preferred Knowledge Skills and Abilities:&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Experience with development in Java Frameworks (.JSF) and J2EE&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; MS-Visio&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; JIRA&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Business Analyst Certificatio</div>', 'Incumbants contract is being renewed for this position', 'C', '6-12 months', '', '', 'Cancelled', 0, 1, 'Tallahassee', 'Florida', 'USA', '2017-06-03 00:00:00', '2017-06-05 09:10:22', '2017-06-19 12:25:15', 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, '', '2017-06-09 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(12124214, 191, -1, 3961, 188, 188, 1, '', 'Senior Project ManagerFDC #8220', 'Senior Project Manager', '<p><br />OIT is seeking the services of an experienced consultant(s) to act as Senior Project Manager and Business Analyst for several strategically aligned enterprise projects. As a Project Manager, the Contractor will have deliverables and direct responsibility for ensuring that all activities associated with the development of enterprise projects are completed on schedule, on budget, and meet the programmatic needs of users to the level of quality required. The contractor will also be responsible for working closely with department staff to analyze and document existing processes, as well as providing a high level of customer support to the department user community. This Project Manager may also be assigned activities surrounding the implementation and support of agency governance and other deliverables, tasks, and/or projects as needed.</p><p>The Senior Project Manager will serve as the principle line of communication for the project team in addition to performing the following activities, included, but not limited to:</p><p>&bull; Develop and manage resource-loaded and leveled project plans;<br />&bull; Maintain project metrics in accordance with established standards;<br />&bull; Serve as a liaison with users;<br />&bull; Provide hands-on leadership for complex projects;<br />&bull; Provide project progress reports to internal and external stakeholders as well as executive leadership;<br />&bull; Manage project spend plans;<br />&bull; Manage resources for associated projects;<br />&bull; Maintain all project artifacts in accordance with PMO standards and other documentation as necessary to ensure compliance with chapter 74-1, Florida Administrative Code;<br />&bull; Lead and/or assist in Business Requirements gathering sessions (JADs);<br />&bull; Work closely with customers, stakeholders and IT software developers to document business requirements;<br />&bull; Develop As-Is, To-Be and other required business analysis documentation;<br />&bull; Lead and develop implementation of business process improvement recommendations;<br />&bull; Follow a standard set of practices that ensure the integrity and quality of project artifacts;<br />&bull; Manage expectations of diverse stakeholders and provide regular briefings to executives;<br />&bull; Work independently as part of a larger cross-functional team.</p><p><br />Education Requirements:<br />Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, Business Administration, or other related field. Or equivalent work experience. Project Management certification or successful completion of a recognized project management curriculum is required.</p><p>Required Qualifications:<br />&bull; PMP Certification;<br />&bull; 5+ years managing successful, large-scale projects that include multiple diverse teams;<br />&bull; 5+ years using Microsoft Project to track and maintain projects;<br />&bull; 5+ years developing and maintaining detailed project plans based on work breakdown structures;<br />&bull; 5+ years&rsquo; experience with PMO methodologies and documentation;<br />&bull; 5+ years with meeting facilitation and documentation;<br />&bull; 5+ years creating and presenting internal and external status reports;<br />&bull; 5+ years with Risk and Issue Management;<br />&bull; Proven skills in working cooperatively and successfully with public sector clients and their stakeholders;<br />&bull; Experience completing project deliverables within scope, schedule, costs and quality constraints;<br />&bull; Ability to coordinate numerous project teams and effectively conduct the initiative to meet overall objectives;<br />&bull; Strong communication and collaborative skills;<br />&bull; Excellent leadership and negotiation skills;<br />&bull; Advanced verbal and written communication skills.<br /><br />NOTE: In addition to the above list, all selected candidates must successfully complete a Level II Background Check.</p><p>Preferred Qualifications:<br />&bull; ITIL Service Management Foundations Certified;<br />&bull; Experience working with technical programming teams;<br />&bull; Take charge, can-do attitude;<br />&bull; Negotiation and/or mediation skills;<br />&bull; Facilitation skills;<br />&bull; Experience with state government projects;<br />&bull; Experience using Offender Based Information System (OBIS);<br />&bull; Knowledge of IT standards in a criminal justice environment;<br />&bull; Experience managing projects in a criminal justice environment.</p>', 'FDC decided to renew the contacts of the current incumbants for these positions.', 'C', '0-6 months', '', '', 'Cancelled', 0, 1, 'Tallahassee', 'Florida', 'USA', '2017-06-02 00:00:00', '2017-06-05 10:07:11', '2017-06-19 12:25:02', 0, 0, 0, 1, NULL, '', '2017-06-08 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
