(12124217, 192, -1, 3958, 192, 192, 1, '', 'Database Analyst / Associate/INDOT/47212/', '', '<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_GoBack" title="_GoBack"></a>Traffic Statistics Analyst</p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">This position will be performing analysis on various\r\ndatabase sources to include: access, excel, GIS, and INDOTs Traffic Count\r\nDatabase System (TCDS).&nbsp; Updates will be\r\nmade to TCDS and GIS systems based on findings.&nbsp;\r\nThis position will also have responsibility for assisting with the\r\npreparation of Turning Movement Forecasts which requires compiling historic\r\ndata from multiple sources and analyzing data using Excel. It is hoped that the\r\nperson would be able to develop scripts or other programmatic tools to\r\nstreamline the preparation of forecasts. This person will assist in the annual\r\npreparation of data for submittal to Highway Performance Monitoring System\r\n(HPMS), including development of Annual Factors, updating of default traffic\r\nvolumes, and preparation of HPMS reports. This person should have a solid\r\nworking knowledge of data analysis through various sources and a basic\r\nunderstanding of ESRI ArcGIS analysis methodologies. The candidate will also\r\nhave basic knowledge of creating macros in Office products with VBA and a basic\r\nknowledge of Python programming. </p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Description of\r\nDuties:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: Symbol">&middot;<span style="font-variant-numeric: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: ''Times New Roman''">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->Data analysis and comparisons form various database types (40%\r\nof the time)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-indent: -0.25in" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: Symbol">&midd