(12124220, 1265, -1, 3961, 188, 188, 1, '', 'Systems Admin Libra #7440', 'Libra Systems Administrator', 'Responsibilities:<div>Providing structured analysis of business processes&nbsp;<br /><div>&bull; Managing user accounts and access to systems&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Technical research and evaluation of technologies, tools, databases,\r\nmethods&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Analysis of detailed requirements and documentation&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Programming and implementing solutions for business requirements&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Contributor on project planning, organization, implementation</div><div>&nbsp;&bull; Contributor to risk identification, tracking, analysis&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Contributor to issue management and tracking&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Working with IT staff and end-user customers to resolve issues and when\r\nneeded, to help design system enhancements&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Effective communication among project stakeholders,&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Coordinate activities with FDLE staff required to support the project&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Provide assistance to FDLE staff in the preparation of procurement\r\ndocuments, evaluation of systems, proposals, and designs&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Provide biweekly status reports to the supervisor</div></div><div><br /></div><div>Mandatory Requirements:&nbsp;</div><div>Minimum of 15 years of experience as a Systems Administrator on successful,\r\nenterprise level information technology projects;&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Extensive experience with Unisys Clear Path Mainframe systems.&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Extensive knowledge of FCIC message keys and protocols.&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Performs analysis and troubleshooting of system defects and issues.&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Designs quality control and test procedures. Applies technical expertise to\r\ntest system solutions.&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Uses defined procedures to configure, test and debug software.\r\nInvestigates, analyzes and resolves problems on software products.&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Requires minimal supervision from more senior resources, handles day-to-day\r\noperations, troubleshooting and performance tuning of systems in area of\r\nresponsibility.&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Gathers and evaluates client capabilities and needs.</div><div>&bull; Assists with services/products/technology solution architecture design\r\nSOW 17-18-042 3\r\nand installation.&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Accountable to upper management for all phases of specific projects.</div><div>&nbsp;&bull; Experience with meeting facilitation and documentation;</div><div><br /></div><div>Experience with:&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Unisys ClearPath MCP&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Metalogic Supervisor &amp; Jampack&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; DSI Tape Library Management&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Progeni Installation &amp; Troubleshooting</div><div>&nbsp;&bull; Knowledge of CCH and FCIC connection protocols</div><div>&bull; FCIC Message Keys&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; DMSII</div><div>&bull; Network Packet Sniffing and Analysis&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Migration of systems to new ClearPath platforms&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Experience in integration of multiple systems or applications&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Experience automating data sharing processes</div><div><br /></div><div>Preferred Skills &amp; Abilities:</div><div>COBOL74&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; ALGOL&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; MCP Installations&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; BL PACK, BL LIB, BL SOURCE&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Unix-basic scripting and commands&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Basic understanding of Computerized Criminal History applications&nbsp;</div><div>&bull; Account Management in Computerized Criminal History applications,\r\nunderstanding roles and privilege frameworks to comply with federal criminal\r\njustice information standards&nbsp;</div>', 'Manager chose to stick with current incumbant', 'C', '0-3 months', '', '', 'Cancelled', 0, 1, 'talahassee', 'Florida', 'USA', '2017-06-02 00:00:00', '2017-06-06 15:26:41', '2017-0